> whis bei ng using for toster and alerts

Right now we are **not using any toaster library**.

Current alerts are simple custom inline messages using Angular signals:

```ts
readonly error = signal('');
readonly success = signal('');
```

Then in template:

```html
@if (error()) {
  <div class="error">{{ error() }}</div>
}

@if (success()) {
  <div class="success">{{ success() }}</div>
}
```

Styled in:

```text
admin-angular/src/styles.css
```

Classes:

```css
.error { ... }
.success { ... }
```

So currently:

- Errors = inline red alert box
- Success = inline green alert box
- No toast popup
- No external package

If we want real toast notifications later, best Angular option would be:

```text
ngx-toastr
```

But for now I kept it lightweight to avoid adding extra dependency.

